SIMPLE: perambulator
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perambulator
<hw>Per*am"bu*la`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who perambulates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A surveyor's instrument for measuring distances. It
consists of a wheel arranged to roll along over the ground, with an
apparatus of clockwork, and a dial plate upon which the distance
traveled is shown by an index. See <er>Odometer</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A low carriage for a child, propelled by pushing; a
baby carriage; -- called also <altname>pram</altname>, in
Britain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perameles</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
